* Error handling with filesystem operations

I will spend some time studying these topics before continuing development.

---

## Another Bug - Unicode File Names

I also discovered that not every file name is written in English.

Windows files can contain:

* Hindi characters
* Japanese characters
* Chinese characters
* Special Unicode symbols

I was originally using `std::string`.

This caused problems when reading file names containing non-English characters.

The solution is to use `std::wstring` and wide-character APIs where necessary so that file names can be handled correctly regardless of language.

This was something I had never thought about before.

---

## Thoughts

Today was mostly debugging and research rather than building new features.

Even though it feels slow, I am learning how real software behaves outside of simple tutorial projects. Windows filesystems contain all kinds of edge cases, and handling them correctly is much harder than I expected.

I am still learning C++ while building WinSloth, so mistakes are expected. Every error I fix teaches me something new.

Maybe years from now I will read this developer log again and laugh at these problems, but right now this is where the journey starts.

This is the beginning of WinSloth.

This is the beginning of VoidMain.


